OL,3,CWhat is Scotland's 'not proven'
OL,4,Cverdict and why could it be scrapped?
OL,6,FIt only exists in Scottish courts, but
OL,7,Fsome campaigners have long raised
OL,8,Fconcerns that it denies victims and
OL,9,Ftheir families justice.
OL,11,FBut what is a 'not proven' verdict,
OL,12,Fand what do its detractors have to say
OL,13,Fabout the Scottish practice?
OL,15,FWhat is the not proven verdict?
OL,17,FScotland is currently the only country
OL,18,Fin the world with such a verdict,
OL,19,Fmeaning jurors in a trial have three
OL,20,Foptions - guilty, not guilty or not
OL,21,Fproven.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
