OL,3,CWhat is Scotland's 'not proven'
OL,4,Cverdict and why could it be scrapped?
OL,6,FThis unique verdict system dates back
OL,7,Fto the 1600s, when juries were asked
OL,8,Fto deliver a verdict of proven or not
OL,9,Fproven and over time, Scots law
OL,10,Fevolved to create this unique three
OL,11,Fverdict system.
OL,13,FNot guilty and not proven are both
OL,14,Facquittals and are used when a jury
OL,15,Fdecides the prosecution has failed to
OL,16,Fprove a case beyond a reasonable
OL,17,Fdoubt, but, unusually, there is no
OL,18,Fformal definition for not proven.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
