OL,3,CWhat is Scotland's 'not proven'
OL,4,Cverdict and why could it be scrapped?
OL,6,FIt is seen as a legal limbo and can be
OL,7,Fan indicator that a jury believes
OL,8,Fsomething happened, without enough
OL,9,Fevidence to convict.
OL,11,FWhy is not proven so contentious?
OL,13,FFor decades, it has been a highly
OL,14,Fcontentious topic, especially for
OL,15,Fvictims and their families who feel it
OL,16,Fallows a jury to avoid committing to a
OL,17,Fguilty decision.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
