OL,3,CWhat is Scotland's 'not proven'
OL,4,Cverdict and why could it be scrapped?
OL,6,F"For victims and survivors of crime, a
OL,7,Fnot proven verdict feels like a denial
OL,8,Fof their experience. It offers no
OL,9,Fclosure, clarity, or comfort. Instead,
OL,10,Fit leaves open-ended questions and
OL,11,Fdeep emotional scars. For the accused,
OL,12,Fwe are told it can cast a shadow of
OL,13,Fsuspicion over them for the rest of
OL,14,Ftheir lives that they feel unable to
OL,15,Faddress.
OL,17,F"Its abolition would mark a milestone
OL,18,Fin the journey toward a more just and
OL,19,Fcompassionate Scottish legal system `
OL,20,Fone that puts the rights and wellbeing
OL,21,Fof victims at its heart."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
