OL,6,FHe believes there was enough evidence
OL,7,Fto find Owens guilty, but thinks that
OL,8,Fhaving the option of 'not proven' gave
OL,9,Fthe jurors a route out of committing.
OL,11,F"The supply of class A, the failure to
OL,12,Fphone an ambulance, fleeing the
OL,13,Fscene... but the country he found
OL,14,Fhimself in, in Scotland, he got
OL,15,Flucky," he said.
OL,17,F"It doesn't address the crime or help
OL,18,Fthe victims; it just helps the jury
OL,19,Fmembers come to a decision."
