OL,3,CWhat is Scotland's 'not proven'
OL,4,Cverdict and why could it be scrapped?
OL,6,F"Research shows there is likely to be
OL,7,Fmore verdicts of guilty, and the
OL,8,Fconcern is, for example, in many
OL,9,Fcriminal cases, which are often
OL,10,Femotive, that it results in jurors
OL,11,Fthat may be more capable of being
OL,12,Fswayed towards a guilty than a not
OL,13,Fguilty verdict."
OL,15,FVictims' support groups have argued it
OL,16,Fallows the guilty to walk free -
OL,17,Fespecially in cases of sexual assault
OL,18,For violence.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/13
